messages.message: Is there an update on this @Rahul Rawal?
didn't get time to look into this. Picking this up now.
I am not able to reproduce this error on sandbox/uat/prod. @Sławek Biel can you confirm?

No, I see it aihub-sandbox. Steps to reproduce
1. create a new project
2. turn “Object detection” on
3. switch to multi step model
4. ask a question like “what’s the income tax?”
All the search queries come up empty
Followed the steps, can not reproduce the issue.
do you see search queries working when you expand Show steps?
No, it’s not working correctly for you. All the Output there is empty, you are supposed to see a list of pages where the the query was found
You can run the same thing without FR to see the difference
Turns out lines are incorrectly mapped to page numbers
You are only getting Page 1 output because all the lines point to page 0. If it worked correctly you’d see many pages
~@Sławek Biel is your local running? Can you try reproducing it there? I do not see this error on my local:~

@Sławek Biel ,
• I have confirmed the line_to_page output in the record markdown metadata to be correct.
• I took first 74 pages out of this 75 paged document, digitised it and ran the query, the query ran perfectly fine.
• I tried the same method with various ranges, for some it works, for some it does not.
Turns out that FR digitisation is working correctly. Can you investigate further?
